Captured building, where mass parties were organized, evacuated
Capturers occupied 11 of the 13 floors of the building on Balmes Street, 51
12 occupiers left the building yesterday at noon without a struggle.
It seems that the nightmare of the neighbors living in 51 Balmes Street is over.
Twelve people left the building yesterday at noon voluntarily, which they illegally occupied and where they organized mass parties that irritated neighbours, by court order without police intervention.
When the operation was completed, the lock on the door was changed to prevent a recurrence of the situation.
"From now on, there'll be a security pass," said the manager.
The squatters who took 11 of the 13 floors of the building, the rest were occupied, took all the electricity and part of the water, painted the walls and left traces of various kinds, especially liquor cans.
The first three floors were a venue for mass parties that lasted up to two days and irritated the owners.
Right outside the building is a nightclub, Balmes 51, which was also damaged.
The owner, Maria Pantinat, told Europe Press that her income had fallen by 80 per cent since the building was occupied.
The club owner says the invaders dragged her into an unfair competition because they sold drinks for three euros, whereas at the club for ten.
In addition, the owner of the discotheque had to respond to the neighbors' complaints about noise, although, as she noted, the noise was caused not by club visitors, but by the residents of the squat and, above all, by those who attended the parties that organized them, whose frequency and intensity increased, as the angry neighbours said.
The owner of the club said the inconvenience was so great that she even reached an agreement with the owner of the property, and for nine months now he's been forgiving her rent.
The City Police also confirmed that in recent weeks they had received more complaints from neighbours about the situation.
The chairman of the municipal group PP, Counsellor Alberto Fernand Díaz, demanded last week “to evacuate the building immediately to solve the problems of coexistence and common spirit among the neighbours and the degradation in this area”.
The popular leader explained that, until summer, only one floor of the building was occupied, but in the last few months, the squatters had invaded all floors and almost every room, and that some of them had been broken into.
In this sense, he added that “it is necessary to put an end to impunity and to resist the culture of the building”.
So, yesterday, the police evacuated the building to Know Barris.
At 3.30 p.m., the police left for Montral Street, 35 after receiving a call from a neighbor who noticed four people entering the building.
Four were arrested immediately.
