He was without a beard, dressed as a local farmer, with no glasses and much thinner.
But prints don't lie.
Using the magnifying glass, ink, spade, and flashlight, Elizar matched the body's fingerprints to those in the photos.
His eyes didn't fail, it was Alfonso Cano.
